the following is the line causing the error on the stack-trace on chrome debug console;
```var Themeable = vue__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_0___default.a.extend().extend({```

it does, I've added  a parent component to test passing new colors;

```python
@solara.component
def Page(color: str):
    _my_reactive = solara.use_reactive(color)
    my_reactive = solara.use_memo(lambda: MyReactive(color), dependencies=[_my_reactive.value])

    solara.Select(label='choose color', value=my_reactive.value, values=my_reactive.get_values(), on_value=my_reactive.set)
    solara.Text(str(my_reactive.value))
    solara.Div(style='height:50px')


@solara.component
def ParentPage():
    color, set_color = solara.use_state('red')
    solara.Select(label='parent select', value=color, on_value=set_color, values=['red', 'green'])

    Page(color)

ParentPage()
```

but this also seem to work:

```python
@solara.component
def Page(color: str):
    def mkreactive():
        return MyReactive(color)
    my_reactive = solara.use_memo(mkreactive, [color])

    solara.Select(label='choose color', value=my_reactive.value, values=my_reactive.get_values(), on_value=my_reactive.set)
    solara.Text(str(my_reactive.value))
```

why would i need `_my_reactive` ?

yes, by overriding the default for the appLayout usinng a custom Layout:
